<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="623" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d623">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10271: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-29T18:00:00-05:00">September 29, 1937—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>238. Your 421, September 27, 5 p.m., first sentence. Telegram
                                received this morning from authoritative source states that on
                                September 28 eleven Japanese bombers raided Nanking and dropped
                                bombs in the vicinity of the Commercial Air Field.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>